%I A395987 #10 May 13 2026 12:12:27
%S A395987 1,2,2,1,2,7,6,1,1,1,1
%N A395987 Number of transmission-minimal connected cubic graphs on 2n vertices.
%C A395987 Here, transmission means the Wiener index, the sum of distances between all unordered pairs of vertices.
%C A395987 The terms a(3)-a(11) are the entries in the "# of graphs" row of Table 1 of Knor, Škrekovski, and Tepeh (2019).
%H A395987 M. Knor, R. Škrekovski and A. Tepeh, <a href="https://match.pmf.kg.ac.rs/electronic_versions/Match81/n1/match81n1_119-132.pdf">Chemical Graphs with the Minimum Value of Wiener Index</a>,  MATCH Commun. Math. Comput. Chem. 81 (2019), 119-132.
%H A395987 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/notebooks/GraphTheory/Transmission-MinimalRegularGraph.nb">Transmission-Minimal Regular Graph</a>.
%e A395987 a(2) = 1, since the tetrahedral graph K_4 is the unique transmission-minimal connected cubic graph on 4 vertices.
%e A395987 a(7) = 7, since there are 7 transmission-minimal connected cubic graphs on 14 vertices.
%Y A395987 Cf. A395986 (minimal transmission for cubic graphs).
%Y A395987 Cf. A395988 (minimal transmission for quartic graphs).
%Y A395987 Cf. A395989 (number of transmission-minimal quartic graphs).
%K A395987 nonn,more,new
%O A395987 2,2
%A A395987 _Eric W. Weisstein_, May 13 2026
